tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE EntanglementRelations (
    relation_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    particle1_id UUID,
    particle2_id UUID,
    entanglement_strength DECIMAL,
    FOREIGN KEY (particle1_id) REFERENCES QuantumParticles(particle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (particle2_id) REFERENCES QuantumParticles(particle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE EntanglementHistory (
    history_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    relation_id UUID,
    measurement_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    measurement_result VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (relation_id) REFERENCES EntanglementRelations(relation_id)
);

CREATE TABLE entanglement (
    entanglement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    particle1_id INT,
    particle2_id INT,
    measure_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (particle1_id) REFERENCES particles(particle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (particle2_id) REFERENCES particles(particle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    particle_id INT,
    entanglement_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (particle_id) REFERENCES particles(particle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (entanglement_id) REFERENCES entanglement(entanglement_id)
);

CREATE TABLE entanglement_details (
    entanglement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    particle1_id INT NOT NULL,
    particle2_id INT NOT NULL,
    entanglement_strength FLOAT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (particle1_id) REFERENCES particles(particle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (particle2_id) REFERENCES particles(particle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE entanglement_history (
    history_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    observation_date DATE NOT NULL,
    entanglement_id INT NOT NULL,
    observation_details TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (entanglement_id) REFERENCES entanglement_details(entanglement_id)
);
